Hmm.  I've had a few similar experiences, but I don't trust my unconscious
processing that far.  I want everything checked via (painfully slow)
conscious, sequential analysis before I change anything that fundamental.  I
remember spending several days chewing over the consequences of some of the
big realizations.

Most people don't even go that far.  If we translate "fundamental values" as
"what criteria are used in selecting and prioritizing goals", we can see
why.  It takes an awfully big shock to trigger a re-evaluation of something
that fundamental, and most people have a strong conservative impulse that
limits changes to a small scale in most situations.

