IMO, Vinge has accomplished a rather unusual feat with this book: he has
taken a future considered wildly optimistic by most people, and shown it to
be a dystopia.  Perhaps he hopes to spur traditional SF fans to the kind of
consideration you suggest.

> So does Vinge present a plausible detailed picture?  I'm not sure..
