Vinge has suggested elsewhere that the Zones actually are limitations on
computation.  In that case we might expect that in the Beyond, some new
kind of computational physics comes into play.  Maybe it is possible to
make a new kind of computer which solves NP complete problems efficiently.
Those computers would be used to create AI and also to solve the problems
needed for FTL travel.  It would streamline programming and so get past
the complexity bottleneck.

> More puzzling was the failure to achieve anything like nanotech.  
> I suppose complexity limits could be behind this.  In one case, 
> a system with "a technology as high as Humankind ever attained" 
