The purposes of guns are three fold:
a) hunting
b) deterring the violation of the rights of one's self, family, property and
state
c) being there for use against opressors when deterrence fails

It is not possible to use cigarettes safely, for example. Automobiles are almost
never used purposely to kill people, yet they do so unpurposefully and
'accidentally' far more than guns do. It is a tool which is unsafe when in
normal use. It is a device which is designed to travel at over 100 mph, yet has
such a lack of safety features that it is frequently fatal to crash in one above
30 mph. Accidents at normal highway speeds are fatal more often than not. This
means that cars are unsafe in normal use.

