If we assume our mind is an information processor, and we further
assume that it is a Turing equivalent machine, even given excessive
use of pseudo-random number generators, any sequence of events could
be exactly duplicated given the same sensor and effector data starting
from the same initial state of the machine.  Free will is thus a
