Not at all.  If Eric Watt Forste changes his list to include the
Moonies, I will cease to cite it.  And the reason is not that these
people are In Charge Of Extropians, or even that they are looked upon as
natural leaders, but because these are the people who make posts, write
Web pages, argue points - people who not only take the name of Extropian
(or not) but exert efforts focusing on that definition, and, through
those efforts, create most of the pattern in the Extropian ideosphere.

No superiority is implied.  If someone or something else exerts a
stronger influence on the "group" - not intragroup politics or authority
within the group, you understand, but metagroup information like
group-image and internally perceived membership criteria - then I'd junk
the list.

