Hey, Eliezer, I think Natasha already has this base covered, although with
a bit more moderation in content, but far more ambitious in range of
distribution -- Natasha's phrase "We Are Transhumans" is well on its way
outward in the solar system aboard the Cassini spacecraft.

Also, this reminds me of The Extropian Declaration that Tom and I wrote way
back in the very early days of Extropy magazine (it was written no later
than 1990, maybe 1989). Remember that we wrote it in the spirit of fun.
(*Please* don't anyone complain about lack of philosophical rigor!) It's
written in the form of a memo to the universe at large.

