I had no intention of interfering or intruding in any way. I simply pointed
out to Randall that it would serve transhuman extropy better to fund
intelligence augmentation, bionic engineering, and synthetic evolution
rather than salvaging unavoidable obsolescence.

>As for whether people should sign up in the first place - well, this is a
>perfect example of the sort of things people should be free to decide for
