scratch.

>Yes, I really don't care much about the future as much as I would if I
>knew I would be a part of it. Existing as a historical footnote is not
>my idea of immortality.

You have to die sometime, whether in a hundred years or a hundred billion
years. But don't worry, historical footnotes will also disappear eventually.
Don't blame me, I didn't make the rules. It doesn't have anything to do with
"deathism" because everbody dies no matter what they believe. Trying to
change that parallels trying to change the laws of thermodynamics.

Only natural law never dies. By natural law I mean the fundamental
principles of existence, laws of physics and chemistry. So to the degree
humans incorporate natural law in their lives, they attain immortality.

Cheers,

--J. R.


