I recently read a short bio of Land, inventor of the Polaroid camera, that
described him as an "incurable optimist."  That hackneyed phrase led me to
wonder:  Might one describe an Extropian as a "*curable* optimist"?

Certainly, no Extropian would want to embrace *fatal* optimism, the sort of
blind faith in the face of all contrary evidence that leads to irretrievable
loss of personal identity.  But what about chronic, non-fatal optimism?  "By
reason! That's the 17th time straight that watching MST3K reruns has not
resulted in my transcendence.  Ah, well, pass the Doritos and I'll have
another go."

T.O. Morrow

