I am going to take a shot at starting a discussion of issues relevant to
immediate choices.  In particular, the "What needs doing" message that
will follow.  If people follow up with ideological disputes, the message
will not yield results.

Initial subject line:
"NOW:  What needs doing [Yudkowsky]"

Replies along the lines of "I don't think you should do that for
<ultimate goals reason>", or anything else concerning the futuristic
scenario, should change to ">H:  *I* think nanotech is wonderful!"

Replies with your own set of projects should change to "NOW:  What needs
doing [MyName]".

If each and every project is not something that you could start doing
NOW, legally, with modern technology, please change the subject line to
"LATER:  What needs doing [MyName]".  For example, "Let's genetically
engineer mosquitoes to carry an antiagathic" is LATER.  "Let's
investigate the possibility of using mosquitoes as cheap measles
vaccinations" would be NOW.  Items that need a billion dollars in
funding are okay; but, insofar as I don't think anyone with that kind of
money is reading the list, please suggest, say, that the foundation be
started with a million and that this seed money be used to seek funding
from the major Internet tycoons.  Ta-da!  It's NOWed.

